excerpt: History of the flour industry told through interactive exhibits in the rebuilt ruins of an old mill.
detail_description: Mill City Museum is a captivating destination that offers an immersive experience into the history of Minneapolis and the flour industry. Housed within the reconstructed ruins of the Washburn "A" Mill, visitors can explore interactive exhibits that narrate the city's evolution alongside the flour industry. The museum, located on the banks of the Mississippi Riverfront, provides insight into how this industry shaped Minneapolis' growth. As part of the St.
name: Mill City Museum

excerpt: Acclaimed venue featuring contemporary art in a variety of media, plus a sculpture garden & bistro.
detail_description: The Walker Art Center is a renowned venue showcasing contemporary art in various forms, along with a sculpture garden and bistro. While not always free, visitors can take advantage of events like Target Free Thursday Nights and First Free Saturdays for complimentary access to exhibitions, lectures, film screenings, and live performances. The center offers diverse experiences for art enthusiasts and families alike.
name: Walker Art Center

excerpt: 5,000-year span of fine & decorative arts ranging from a mummy to paintings by European masters.
detail_description: The Minneapolis Institute of Art, also known as Mia, is a renowned art museum boasting over 90,000 works from six continents spanning 5,000 years. Housed in a stunning Prairie Architecture building designed by legends like Louis Sullivan and Frank Lloyd Wright, Mia offers an open floor plan to showcase its diverse collections. Visitors can explore ancient artifacts like a mummy and European masterpieces alongside contemporary exhibits featuring artists such as Dawoud Bey and Kehinde Wiley.
name: Minneapolis Institute of Art

excerpt: This modern stainless steel & brick building houses American & contemporary paintings plus ceramics.
detail_description: The Weisman Art Museum, designed by the renowned architect Frank O. Gehry, is a modern stainless steel and brick building located near the Mississippi River on the University of Minnesota campus. The museum's stunning exterior often draws attention from visitors due to its unique design, especially at sunset. Inside, it houses a diverse collection of over 25,000 works of art including American and contemporary paintings, ceramics, Korean furniture, and special exhibitions throughout the year.
name: Weisman Art Museum
address: 333 E River Rd, Minneapolis, MN 55455, USA

excerpt: Biking & walking paths on this former railroad bridge with panoramic views of St. Anthony Falls.
detail_description: Stone Arch Bridge, located in downtown Minneapolis at the intersection of West River Road and Portland Ave, is a historic former railroad bridge that offers stunning panoramic views of St. Anthony Falls. Built in 1883 by James J. Hill, it served as a vital transportation link until 1965 and is now a symbol of the railroad age. This National Historic Engineering Landmark forms part of the two-mile St. Anthony Falls Heritage Trail, featuring pedestrian walkways and bicycle lanes for year-round outdoor enjoyment.
name: Stone Arch Bridge

excerpt: Landmark venue for wide-ranging plays on 3 stages, full-service dining, several bars & river views.
detail_description: The Guthrie Theater, a renowned venue in Minneapolis, offers a diverse range of plays across its three stages. The theater also features full-service dining, multiple bars, and scenic river views. Established in 2006 to replace the original Guthrie Theater near the Walker Art Center, the new facility includes various amenities such as costume and set shops, storage spaces, classrooms, and a gift shop offering unique merchandise.
name: Guthrie Theater

excerpt: Home baseball stadium for the Minnesota Twins offering group & private behind-the-scenes tours.
detail_description: Target Field is the home stadium of the Minnesota Twins and offers both group and private behind-the-scenes tours. The stadium's sleek and modern design, featuring a large Minnie and Paul logo in center field, opened in 2010. Even if you're not there during baseball season, you can still visit the plaza and amphitheater without buying a ticket. Additionally, various restaurants have created attractive patio spaces from old warehouses around the stadium.
name: Target Field

excerpt: Cycling, walking & seasonal wading pools are big draws to these cascading falls in a namesake park.
detail_description: Minnehaha Falls is a stunning 53-foot waterfall located in Minnehaha Park, the most-visited park in Minneapolis. The falls are formed by the Minnehaha Creek, which flows from Lake Minnetonka to the Mississippi River.
name: Minnehaha Falls

excerpt: An 11-acre preserve featuring a conservatory, an arbor & 40+ sculptures by notable modern artists.
detail_description: The Minneapolis Sculpture Garden is an 11-acre urban park adjacent to the Walker Art Center, showcasing over 40 captivating sculptures from renowned modern artists. One of its most iconic pieces is the giant spoon sculpture, Spoonbridge and Cherry by Claes Oldenburg. The garden offers free tours, outdoor concerts, and educational activities for all ages. Open year-round from dawn until midnight, it provides a unique blend of art and nature with its carefully curated landscape supporting wildlife and plants.
name: Minneapolis Sculpture Garden

excerpt: Housed in an old depot, this rock venue & tiny side bar have hosted & launched many acts since 1970.
detail_description: First Avenue is a legendary rock venue and bar located in an old depot that has been a pivotal space for launching musical acts since 1970. It gained fame as the concert hall featured in 'Purple Rain,' where Prince and The Revolution were the house band in the 1980s. Originally known as The Depot, it was ground zero for the local punk and hardcore scene, providing a platform for bands like the Replacements, Husker Du, and Soul Asylum.
name: First Avenue

excerpt: This grand church with stained-glass windows, shrines & an art gallery was America's first basilica.
detail_description: The Basilica of Saint Mary, located in downtown Minneapolis, is a historic Roman Catholic minor basilica and the first basilica established in America. This architectural masterpiece boasts stunning stained-glass windows, shrines, and an art gallery. Constructed in 1915, it is a prime example of Beaux Arts architecture and has been on the National Register of Historic Places since 1975.
name: Basilica of Saint Mary

excerpt: Stately museum & culture center featuring Swedish history exhibits, a mansion & art classes.
detail_description: The American Swedish Institute is a stately museum and culture center that showcases the rich history and heritage of the Scandinavian population in the United States. Established in 1929, it features informative talks, language-learning classes, and temporary exhibits. The institute comprises the modern Nelson Cultural Center and the historic Turnblad Mansion. Every holiday season, it hosts a traditional Scandinavian Christmas marketplace called Jul Shop, offering unique gifts and handcrafted items.
name: American Swedish Institute

excerpt: Museum & education center for all ages offering exhibits on electricity, Ben Franklin & magnets.
detail_description: The Bakken Museum in Minneapolis is a captivating destination for visitors of all ages, offering an engaging exploration of science and innovation. The museum features exhibits on electricity, Ben Franklin, and magnets, showcasing 18th-century gadgets and gizmos introduced at Benjamin Franklin's house parties for scientists. Visitors can also experience a re-creation of Mary Shelley's legendary monster and engage in interactive activities like creating stop-motion movies and virtual art.
name: The Bakken Museum
address: 3537 Zenith Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55416, USA

detail_description: Bauhaus Brew Labs is a must-visit spot in the Northeast, Minneapolis. Located in the arts district, this brewery offers a unique experience with its large patio overlooking train tracks. The addition of Animales Barbeque Co. has enhanced the experience, offering refreshing drinks like Short Pants shandy and pineapple lemonade to complement their flavorful ribs.
name: Bauhaus Brew Labs
address: 1315 Tyler St NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

excerpt: Civil Warâ€“era military structure & museum with a drum corp, historical re-enactments & a gift shop.
detail_description: Historic Fort Snelling is a significant National Historic Landmark that dates back to 1819. It played a crucial role in the founding of St. Paul and was strategically located at the confluence of the Mississippi River and the Minnesota River. The fort features well-preserved bulwarks and palisades, offering insights into Minnesota's military history from pre-Civil War to World Wars I and II, as well as its involvement in fur and slave trade.
name: Historic Fort Snelling
address: 200 Tower Ave, St Paul, MN 55111, USA

excerpt: Historic urban waterfall known for its hydroelectric dam & lock system & heritage trail loop.
detail_description: Saint Anthony Falls, located in Minneapolis, is a historic urban waterfall with a hydroelectric dam and lock system. In the 19th century, it was central to the Flour Milling Capital of the World, powering various mills. The Dakota people considered it a significant site for thousands of years. Overuse and poor engineering led to damage in the late 1800s, prompting improvements by the Army Corps of Engineers.
name: Saint Anthony Falls

detail_description: The Minneapolis Central Library, established in 1885 as the city's first public library, is situated in downtown Minneapolis. It features an extensive children's section and a renowned comic book collection. The Pohlad Hall Theater hosts monthly educational programs for children, offering animated shorts, live entertainment, free books, readings, and refreshments.
name: Minneapolis Central Library

detail_description: The Grand Rounds Scenic Byway is a sprawling network of urban parks in the United States, offering visitors an extensive and picturesque outdoor experience. This renowned byway has been recognized for its historical significance and has been nominated for inclusion on the National Register of Historic Places. With its free entrance, it provides a great opportunity to explore nature within city limits.
name: Grand Rounds Scenic Bywy

excerpt: This lake is surrounded by parks & features beaches, trails, boating, a bandshell & skyline views.
detail_description: Lake Harriet, located in Minneapolis, is a picturesque spot surrounded by parks and offering various recreational activities. Visitors can enjoy beaches, trails, boating, and skyline views. The area is popular during late spring and summer, attracting families and individuals who come to relax by the lake. The lake's charm extends to its nearby cafes where patrons can savor delightful meals amidst a warm ambiance.
name: Lake Harriet

detail_description: U.S. Bank Stadium, located in Minneapolis, is a hub for sports and entertainment. It is home to the Minnesota Vikings NFL team and has hosted major events like Super Bowl LI. The stadium boasts a unique design with a translucent roof and pivoting glass doors, as well as the Legacy Ship featuring fan-donated bricks and historical markers. Visitors can take guided tours to learn about the stadium's history and architecture.
name: U.S. Bank Stadium
